# Next.js App Router

Next.js 16 App Router. Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before changing routing, data fetching, or caching — APIs differ from older versions.

## Structure

- `layout.tsx` — shared shell; `page.tsx` — route UI.
- Add `loading.tsx` / `error.tsx` when those states matter.
- Static assets in `public/`.
- Export `metadata` or `generateMetadata` for SEO.

## Async route props (Next.js 15+)

`searchParams`, `params`, and `headers()` are async — await in Server Components:

```tsx
interface HomeProps {
  searchParams: Promise<{ q?: string }>;
}

export default async function Home({ searchParams }: HomeProps) {
  const { q } = await searchParams;
}
```

## Data fetching

- Fetch MongoDB in Server Components or `src/lib/` — not Client Components.
- Wrap slow UI in `<Suspense>` with a meaningful fallback.
- Catch errors at the page boundary; show user-facing messages.

## File conventions

`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `route.ts`.
